snippet: Miami-Havana tensions are being stoked as two Florida lawmakers seek an inquiry into possible trade embargo violations by the musicians.
abstract: United States Treasury Department officials say that they have begun investigating whether Jay-Z and Beyonce violated trade embargo against Cuba by traveling to the island; officials say they are working in response to demands for more information about trip from Florida Reps Ileana Ros-Lehtinen and Mario Diaz-Balart, both of whom are Cuban-American.
lead_paragraph: Miami-Havana tensions are being stoked as two Florida lawmakers seek an inquiry into possible trade embargo violations by the musicians.

headline.seo: Cuba Trip by Beyoncé and Jay-Z Investigated
headline.main: Trip to Cuba by Beyoncé and Jay-Z Is Investigated
